Load Balancer distributes the web traffic to the available server.
or 
Load Balcing refers to efficient distributing incoming traffic across a group of backends server. 

Four types of load balancer-
1. Application Load Balancer ( Comes in 2012 ) ( Works on Layer 7 ) ( HTTP , HTTPS )
2. Network Load Balancer ( Layer 4 - Transport Layer ) ( TCP and UDP , TLS )
3. Classic Load Balancer ( Previous generation - Aug 22 2022 exit from AWS ) ( HTTP, HTTPS, TCP and TLS )
4. Gateway Load Balancer 
